StageSize is used to provide an inline representation of any stage measurement, whether that be overall stage size, blastzone distance, stage length, or otherwise. There are currently 6 possible levels of size that can be represented:
* {{#invoke:StageSize | main | XS}} 
* {{#invoke:StageSize | main | S}} 
* {{#invoke:StageSize | main | M}} 
* {{#invoke:StageSize | main | L}} 
* {{#invoke:StageSize | main | XL}}
* {{#invoke:StageSize | main | NA}} (Used for situations where the measurement doesn't apply, such as in the case of walkoff blastzones)

This template takes in two possible parameters:
<pre>
{{ StageSize
| first parameter: the size to be used. Can be XS, S, M, L, XL, or NA.
| (optional) second parameter: the text to be styled 
}}
</pre>

For example:
<pre>
{{ StageSize
| XL
| I can put any text in here!
}}
</pre>
{{ StageSize
| XL
| I can put any text in here!
}}

The second parameter is completely optional. If no text is given in that slot, then the word equivalent of that size will be printed out. For example:
<pre>
{{ StageSize
| XS
}}
</pre>
{{ StageSize
| XS
}}

The [[Module:StageSize|Module StageSize]] is wrapped in the [[Template:StageSize|Template StageSize]] to make editing more accessible. Actual edits to the contents of this widget should be done to the Module itself.

